28:["$","section",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold mb-6 flex items-center gap-3","children":[["$","svg",null,{"ref":"$undefined","xmlns":"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg","width":24,"height":24,"viewBox":"0 0 24 24","fill":"none","stroke":"currentColor","strokeWidth":2,"strokeLinecap":"round","strokeLinejoin":"round","className":"lucide lucide-trending-up w-6 h-6 text-emerald-400","children":[["$","polyline","126l90",{"points":"22 7 13.5 15.5 8.5 10.5 2 17"}],["$","polyline","kwv8wd",{"points":"16 7 22 7 22 13"}],"$undefined"]}],"ROI: How Much Revenue Can AI Call Answering Recover?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-6","children":["Let us do the maths. A typical ",["$","a",null,{"href":"/ai-call-answering-plumbers","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:underline","children":"plumber"}]," in the UK receives 8–12 calls per day and misses 5–7 of them while working. At a 50% conversion rate (industry average for trade enquiries) and an average job value of £250, each missed call costs approximately £125 in potential revenue."]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mb-6","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6 text-center","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-2","children":"5"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-white/60 text-sm","children":"Missed calls per day"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6 text-center","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-2","children":"£125"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-white/60 text-sm","children":"Potential revenue per call"}]]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-6 text-center","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-emerald-400 mb-2","children":"£625"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-white/60 text-sm","children":"Lost revenue per day"}]]}]]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-6","children":"That is £3,125 per week, or £162,500 per year in potential revenue. Even if AI call answering only recovers 20% of those missed calls (a conservative estimate), that is £32,500 in additional annual revenue. Against a service cost of £59–£125/month (£708–£1,500/year), the ROI is 2,100% to 4,500%. This is not a cost — it is an investment with measurable returns."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":["For emergency trades (",["$","a",null,{"href":"/ai-call-answering-plumbers","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:underline","children":"plumbers"}],", ",["$","a",null,{"href":"/ai-call-answering-locksmiths","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:underline","children":"locksmiths"}],", ",["$","a",null,{"href":"/ai-call-answering-heating-engineers","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:underline","children":"heating engineers"}],"), the numbers are even more dramatic. Emergency callouts average £150–£400, and callers who cannot reach you will immediately call the next number on Google. Capturing just one additional emergency callout per week pays for the entire monthly service cost."]}]]}]
29:["$","section",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-500/10 to-emerald-600/5 border border-emerald-500/20 rounded-2xl p-8","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-bold mb-4","children":"Which AI Call Answering Service Should You Choose?"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":["For most UK tradespeople, ",["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"whoza.ai"}]," offers the best combination of price, features, and value. The £59 entry price is competitive, but the included WhatsApp delivery, review collection, and competitor analysis turn it from a cost centre into a revenue driver. The 7-day free trial (no card) and 30-day money-back guarantee mean you can test it without risk."]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Clara AI"}]," is the best pure budget option if you just need basic call answering and nothing else. ",["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Moneypenny"}]," remains the choice for high-value commercial clients where human empathy justifies the premium.",["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"IONOS"}]," is a sensible starting point for testing the concept at minimal cost. ",["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"ARROW"}]," works for mid-sized teams wanting a hybrid approach. ",["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"RingCentral AIR"}]," and",["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":" Answer.co.uk"}]," are niche options for specific use cases."]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"The key insight from our testing: the service that captures your calls is just the entry point. The services that also capture reviews, monitor competitors, and deliver to WhatsApp generate compounding returns that dwarf the monthly cost difference. In 2026, AI call answering is not about avoiding missed calls — it is about building a systematic revenue capture machine."}]]}]}]
