49:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"The 3-month minimum contract is also a concern for tradespeople who want flexibility. However, if you simply need basic call answering at the lowest possible price and do not care about reviews, WhatsApp, or competitive intelligence, Clara AI is a solid choice."}]
4a:["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-500/20 text-blue-400 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold","children":"3"}],"Moneypenny Review — Best Human Receptionist"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"Moneypenny is the veteran of this comparison, with 25+ years of experience providing receptionist services to UK businesses. They use real human receptionists, not AI, which means genuine empathy and the ability to handle complex, nuanced enquiries. For high-value commercial clients where every interaction matters, this human touch can justify the premium."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"However, for most tradespeople, the cost is prohibitive. Starting at £150/month and scaling to £400+ for larger volumes, Moneypenny costs 2.5–7x more than AI alternatives. The 12-month contract locks you in, and the 2–5 day setup means you cannot respond to urgent demand spikes. There is no WhatsApp delivery, no review collection, and no competitive intelligence."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":["Moneypenny remains the right choice for luxury trades — high-end builders, bespoke kitchen fitters, commercial electrical contractors — where the human touch is part of the brand promise. For emergency ",["$","a",null,{"href":"/ai-call-answering-plumbers","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:underline","children":"plumbers"}]," and ",["$","a",null,{"href":"/ai-call-answering-locksmiths","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:underline","children":"locksmiths"}]," who need volume and speed, AI services are the better value."]}]]}]
4b:["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-white/10 text-white/60 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold","children":"4"}],"ARROW Review — Best Hybrid Approach"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"ARROW offers a hybrid model combining AI efficiency with human backup for complex calls. At £79–£199/month, it sits in the mid-market and offers CRM integrations, call recording, and lead qualification. The setup takes 1–2 days, which is reasonable."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"The downside is the lack of WhatsApp delivery and review collection, plus the 6-month contract. The AI voice quality is inconsistent — sometimes excellent, sometimes clearly robotic. For mid-sized trade businesses with 3–5 staff who want a hybrid approach, ARROW is a viable option, but whoza.ai offers more features at a lower price point."}]]}]
4c:["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-white/10 text-white/60 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold","children":"5"}],"IONOS Review — Cheapest Entry Point"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"IONOS is the cheapest service we tested at £9.99/month, with no contract and a 14-day trial. For sole traders who want to test AI call answering with minimal risk, this is the lowest barrier to entry. The setup is fast — under an hour — and the SMS delivery works reliably."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"The trade-off is generic AI that is not trained for trade-specific terminology. When we tested with plumbing and electrical enquiries, the AI struggled with technical terms and often misrecorded details. The spam filtering is poor — we received 3 robocall notifications in one day. For a quick test, IONOS works. For a serious business tool, you will quickly outgrow it."}]]}]
4d:["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-white/10 text-white/60 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold","children":"6"}],"RingCentral AIR Review — Enterprise Overkill"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed mb-4","children":"RingCentral AIR is the enterprise giant in this comparison. At £119–£349/month with 12-month contracts, it is designed for larger businesses with complex communication needs. The platform includes video meetings, advanced analytics, and a vast integration ecosystem."}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"For a sole trader or small trade team, this is overkill. The 3–7 day setup is the longest we tested, and the US-focused support can be frustrating for UK-specific issues. There is no WhatsApp integration, no review collection, and the complexity means you will spend more time managing the tool than using it. Only consider this if you have 10+ staff and need enterprise-grade communications infrastructure."}]]}]
4e:["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-white/5 border border-white/10 rounded-xl p-8","children":[["$","h3",null,{"className":"text-xl font-bold mb-4 flex items-center gap-2","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-white/10 text-white/60 flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold","children":"7"}],"Answer.co.uk Review — Unremarkable Middle Ground"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-white/70 leading-relaxed","children":"Answer.co.uk is a UK-based service that offers competent but unremarkable AI call answering. At £95–£295/month with a 6-month contract, it is more expensive than better-featured alternatives. The custom scripts are useful, and call patching works well, but the lack of WhatsApp, reviews, competitor analysis, or trade-specific training makes it hard to justify over whoza.ai or Clara AI. It is not a bad service — it is simply outperformed by competitors at every price point."}]]}]
